{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/carbon-monoxide-poisoning/diagnosis/when-to-suspect-carbon-monoxide-poisoning/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"121276cf-d471-5cb4-b2d7-b924d89cd776","slug":"when-to-suspect-carbon-monoxide-poisoning","fullItemName":"When to suspect carbon monoxide poisoning","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 5565c01d-2aed-4365-ad89-9330b3a89dc3 --><h2>When should I suspect carbon monoxide poisoning?</h2><!-- end field 5565c01d-2aed-4365-ad89-9330b3a89dc3 -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item a6a30a11-464b-4719-b70e-36d08db9ea9d --><!-- begin field ffbd601c-4052-4085-a1b6-027ca5900cd1 --><ul><li><strong>Ask people with possible <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/carbon-monoxide-poisoning/diagnosis/clinical-features/\">symptoms</a> of carbon monoxide poisoning about:</strong><ul><li><strong>C</strong> — co-habitees & co-occupants. If anyone else in the house is affected.</li><li><strong>O </strong>— outdoors. If symptoms improve when they are out of the building.</li><li><strong>M</strong> — maintenance. If their fuel burning appliances and vents are properly maintained.  </li><li><strong>A</strong> — alarm. If they have a carbon monoxide alarm.</li></ul></li><li>Consider carbon monoxide poisoning as a cause of symptoms, particularly if more than one member of a household (including pets) is affected and if symptoms improve on leaving the property.  </li><li><strong>If suspicious of carbon monoxide poisoning, also ask the person if they:</strong><ul><li>Have recently had a heating or cooking appliance installed.</li><li>Ever use the oven or gas stove for heating purposes as well as for cooking.</li><li>Have had any ventilation changes in the home recently (for example, double glazing has been fitted).</li><li>Have noticed any sooty stains around appliances or an increase in condensation. </li><li>Do work which involves possible exposure to smoke, fumes or motor vehicle exhaust at work.</li><li>Live in a home which is detached, semi-detached, terraced, a flat, a bedsit, a hostel or if it's a mobile home.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Suspect carbon monoxide poisoning </strong><strong>when:</strong><ul><li><a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/carbon-monoxide-poisoning/diagnosis/clinical-features/\">Clinical features</a> of poisoning are present.</li><li>Exposure to a potential <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/carbon-monoxide-poisoning/background-information/sources-of-carbon-monoxide/\">source</a> of carbon monoxide has occurred.</li><li>Symptoms correlate with exposure.<ul><li>Symptoms develop following exposure and improve slowly when exposure stops.</li><li>Other people exposed to the same possible source develop similar symptoms correlating with exposure.</li></ul></li></ul></li></ul><!-- end field ffbd601c-4052-4085-a1b6-027ca5900cd1 --><!-- end item a6a30a11-464b-4719-b70e-36d08db9ea9d -->","topic":{"id":"c7d4e6f1-4a64-54dd-be29-5ad7634dc8fc","topicId":"805e4b0d-7153-46dc-ad0e-078747029014","topicName":"Carbon monoxide poisoning","slug":"carbon-monoxide-poisoning","lastRevised":"Last revised in October 2018","chapters":[{"id":"a4fe1221-5744-5f22-a201-02e8b266911e","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"828b1d0e-ea18-5f96-b42a-c314ceef8855","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"9fca25de-4ad7-587a-b4b5-6f05a504ccdb","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"9ed23aaf-6330-5d0c-98c7-1278da260d26","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"2a5a9598-8906-5dcc-b576-387cf1cb47e8","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"d52b952b-ba10-536f-8e68-fef415d54a86","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"d3be2eb0-